Sentencas: Anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell with SrTi(0.98)Nb(0.02)O(3-)anode, yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte and La(Ni0.6Fe0.4)O-3 +/- cathode has been successfully fabricated and evaluated.
Titulo: Application of wet powder spraying for anode supported solid oxide fuel cell with a perovskite SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ anode

Sentencas: Process of anode support fabrication has been presented.
Titulo: Application of wet powder spraying for anode supported solid oxide fuel cell with a perovskite SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ anode

Sentencas: Wet powder spraying and high temperature sintering method have been studied and applied to deposit the thin electrolyte layer.
Titulo: Application of wet powder spraying for anode supported solid oxide fuel cell with a perovskite SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ anode

Sentencas: In order to improve catalytic properties of the anode, it has been impregnated with Ni.
Titulo: Application of wet powder spraying for anode supported solid oxide fuel cell with a perovskite SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ anode

Sentencas: Electrical properties of fuel cells have been measured to determine their performance.
Titulo: Application of wet powder spraying for anode supported solid oxide fuel cell with a perovskite SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ anode

Sentencas: The open cell voltage of 1.08V and maximum power density at the level of 160mWcm(-2) were observed at 800 degrees C. (C) 2013 WILEY-VCH Verlag GmbH & Co. KGaA, Weinheim
Titulo: Application of wet powder spraying for anode supported solid oxide fuel cell with a perovskite SrTi0.98Nb0.02O3-δ anode
